	(text "This circuit replaces the reset logic of the sweep generator by simply plugging into the 74LS90 socket on the PCB and adding a +15V\nsupply pickoff to the main board.  J1 is a 14-pin ribbon cable jumper to that socket.  The sweep generator reset transistors and resistors\nshould be removed, as well as the +5V dropping resistor and filter capacitor.\n\nEnhancements:\n1. The 7.5M potentiometer used in the original circuit is no longer available. This circuit changes from a current sense reset \n   circuit to a digital BCD code reset.  It uses a 10 position rotary switch to set the number of curves desired. The switch has \n   positive detent stops which are more precise than fiddling with a potentiometer and offers repeatable and accurate setting. \n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 25.654 147.066 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.524 1.524)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "9519acc8-ef16-4e1a-bf25-fef28685e8ea")
	)
	(text "3 Curves"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 55.118 61.468 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "a684f8b0-58a4-45d6-a884-2b41382ac1e5")
	)
